.TH Simple_Shell 1 "SEPTEMBER 19, 2023" "ALX SWE Project 0x16_Simple Shell"
.SH NAME
.B Simple_Shell \- A simple UNIX command interpreter written in C

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B Simple_Shell
.RB [ options ]
.RB [ file ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B Simple_Shell
is a command language interpreter that executes commands read from the standard input, designed as a clone of the 'sh' shell.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell always returns the status of the previously executed command (0 if no command was executed). Non-zero values indicate exit failure codes.

.SH PATH
The shell looks in the PATH environment variable to locate executable program files.

.SH INVOCATION
.PP
The
.B Simple_Shell
can be invoked both interactively and non-interactively. When invoked with standard input not connected to a terminal, it reads and executes received commands in order.
.PP
If
.B Simple_Shell
is invoked with standard input connected to a terminal, it opens an interactive shell. When executing interactively, the
.B Simple_Shell
displays the prompt
.B "($) "
when it is ready to read a command.

.SH OPTIONS
There are no specific options for the
.B Simple_Shell.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
To run a command using the
.B Simple_Shell
interactively, use the following syntax:
.RS
.nf
$ ./hsh [command] [options]
$ ls -l
.fi
.RE

.SH BUGS
There are currently no known bugs.

.SH AUTHORS
The
.B Simple_Shell
was created by Joycelyn Arhin and Prince Kongo.

